text.tspan: This is physical pendulum given that the size of the sphere is not small compared to the length of the string. The period of the physical pendulum is given by $$T=2\\pi\\sqrt{\\frac{I_0}{mgh}}$$ where $$I_0$$ is the moment of inertia of the system about the point of rotation and $$h=L+R$$ is the distance of the center of mass of the system to the axis of rotation. To find $$I_0$$ we use the the Steiners theorem, $$\\\\I_0=I_{cm}+mx^2\\\\$$ where $$x$$ is the distance from the center of mass of the sphere to the point of rotation. So, $$\\\\ I_0=\\frac{2}{5}mR^2+m(L+R)^2$$ $$. Therefore, $$\\\\ T=2\\pi\\sqrt{\\frac{\\frac{2}{5}mR^2+m(L+R)^2}{mg(L+R)}}\\\\=T=2\\pi\\sqrt{\\frac{\\frac{2}{5}(\\frac{L}{4})^2+(L+(\\frac{L}{4}))^2}{g(L+(\\frac{L}{4}))}}\\\\=\\frac{\\sqrt{47}{10}\\Big(2\\pi\\sqrt{\\frac{L}{g}}\\Big)$$
